%% Reflects ADR-001: refresh token is opaque (SecureRandom-generated) and
%% DB-backed, not a self-verifying JWT. Its validity is determined entirely
%% by ServiceAuth looking up the corresponding row — there is no signature
%% to verify at the Gateway and no Redis blacklist involved.
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor User
    participant Gateway
    participant ServiceAuth
    participant DB

    User            ->>  Gateway        :   HTTP POST http://server-gateway/refresh <br/>RefreshTokenRequest
    Gateway         ->>  ServiceAuth    :   HTTP POST http://service-auth/api/v1/auth/refresh <br/>RefreshTokenRequest
    ServiceAuth     ->>  DB             :   SELECT refresh_token WHERE token = ?
    DB              -->> ServiceAuth    :   result
    alt Not found / expired
        ServiceAuth -->> Gateway        :   HTTP 401 Unauthorized
        Gateway     -->> User           :   HTTP 401 Unauthorized
    else Found and valid
        ServiceAuth ->>  DB             :   DELETE old refresh_token row (rotation)
        ServiceAuth ->>  DB             :   INSERT new refresh_token row
        ServiceAuth -->> Gateway        :   HTTP 200 OK RefreshTokenResponse <br/>(new access + refresh token)
        Gateway     -->> User           :   HTTP 200 OK RefreshTokenResponse
    end
